"title": "1657: numbers, fractions",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1657: numbers, fractions",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Mainly associated with divisions of the people and of property, and also with sacrificial offerings.</p>\n<h2>One half</h2>\n<h3>Half the people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:33\">JOS 8:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:12-Deut27:13\">DEU 27:12–27:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:21\">1KI 16:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:16\">NEH 4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:31-Neh12:32\">NEH 12:31–12:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:38\">NEH 12:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:24\">NEH 13:24</a></p>\n<h3>The half-tribes of Manasseh</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:13\">DEU 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:33\">NUM 32:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:13-Num34:14\">NUM 34:13–34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:8\">DEU 29:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:29-Josh13:31\">JOS 13:29–13:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:10\">JOS 22:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:23\">1CH 5:23</a></p>\n<h3>Halves in offering sacrifices</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:10\">GEN 15:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:6\">EXO 24:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:13\">EXO 30:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:20\">LEV 6:20</a></p>\n<h3>Significant examples of halves</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:4\">2SA 10:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr19:4\">1CH 19:4</a> <em>David's men and the Ammonites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:25\">1KI 3:25</a> <em>Solomon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:7\">1KI 10:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:6\">2CH 9:6</a> <em>the Queen of Sheba</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:3\">EST 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth7:2\">EST 7:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:23\">MRK 6:23</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:16-Isa44:20\">ISA 44:16–44:20</a> <em>Idolatry</em></p>\n<h2>One third</h2>\n<h3>Thirds of a group</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:2\">2SA 18:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:5-2Kgs11:6\">2KI 11:5–11:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:4-2Chr23:5\">2CH 23:4–23:5</a></p>\n<h3>Thirds in the processes of judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:18\">REV 9:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek5:2\">EZK 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek5:12\">EZK 5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:7-Rev8:12\">REV 8:7–8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:15\">REV 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:4\">REV 12:4</a></p>\n<h2>One fifth</h2>\n<h3>A fifth of the harvest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:34\">GEN 41:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:24\">GEN 47:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:26\">GEN 47:26</a></p>\n<h3>A fifth in cases of restitution</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:14-Lev5:16\">LEV 5:14–5:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:5\">LEV 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:14\">LEV 22:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:7\">NUM 5:7</a></p>\n<h3>Redeeming what is promised to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:13\">LEV 27:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:15\">LEV 27:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:19\">LEV 27:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:27\">LEV 27:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:31\">LEV 27:31</a></p>\n<h2>One tenth</h2>\n<h3>Instructions about God's tithe</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:30-Lev27:32\">LEV 27:30–27:32</a></strong> <em>The term “tithe” is the Old English word for “one tenth”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:21\">NUM 18:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:26\">NUM 18:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:6\">DEU 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:11\">DEU 12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:22\">DEU 14:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:38\">NEH 10:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:4\">AMO 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:8-Mal3:10\">MAL 3:8–3:10</a></p>\n<h3>The royal tithe</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:15\">1SA 8:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:17\">1SA 8:17</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of the tithe</h3>\n<p>Abraham:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:20\">GEN 14:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:1-Heb7:10\">HEB 7:1–7:10</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:22\">GEN 28:22</a> <em>Jacob</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:5-2Chr31:6\">2CH 31:5–31:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:12\">2CH 31:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:37\">NEH 10:37</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:23\">MAT 23:23</a> <em>teachers of the law and Pharisees</em></p>",
